<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-09-10T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-09-10T16:00:00-05:00" n="670" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d670">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">693.119/281: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-10T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">September 10,
                                        1919, 5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your August 30, 5 p.m. Department has interpreted your 2760 of May 19,
                                1919,<note n="99" xml:id="d670fn99">Not printed; substance conveyed
                                to the Department by despatch No. 2725, of May 10, <ref target="#pg_669">p. 669</ref>.</note> as including raw material
                            for manufacture of arms and ammunition and has only recently held it to
                            include the machinery used in their manufacture.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>